results.name: Number of labeled graphs covering the vertex set {1,...,n} with no crossing edges.
comment: Two edges {x,y}, {z,t} are crossing if either x < z < y < t or z < x < t < y. If the vertices are arranged in a circle, this is equivalent to crossing of chords.
Covering means there are no isolated vertices.
link: Gus Wiseman, The a(4) = 25 graphs covering {1,2,3,4} with no crossing edges.
Gus Wiseman, The a(5) = 176 graphs covering 5 vertices with no crossing edges, radial embedding.
